result.formatted_address: G/F The Centrium, 60 Wyndham Street, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Bungalow

reviews.text: Service is terrible. Made a reservation for 9:30 and start calling you 3 times starting from 9pm, 9:15 and 9:25. Smells like sweat inside the restaurant. Waitress lose patient when getting our order. Soup is not hot but slightly warm. However pasta is hot.

They charge any guy that looks like a foreigner $300 HKD, but any guy who doesn't look like a foreigner (and white men) are free, which I find to be extremely racist. The bouncer as well said, "I hate tourists," but he was Indian?? I went inside for a bit and their music sucked. At least ladies are free.
Great location, restaurant during the day (food are server in the afternoon and at night) , and turn into a club after 11pm
Beer is hot. WTF
Nice, quiet location during the day. Pleasant staff and reasonably priced drinks. Great place to stop off for refreshments when you're exploring Hong Kong.
